{"cursor":"18792","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nAn 'isolation tank' is a lightless, soundproof tank inside which subjects float\nin salt water at skin temperature. They were first used by John C.\nLilly Lilly, John C. & E.J. Gold (2000). Tanks for the Memories: Flotation\nTank Talks. Gateways Books & Tapes. ISBN 0-89556-071-2 in 1954 to test the\neffects of sensory deprivation. Such tanks are now also used for meditation and\nrelaxation and in alternative medicine. The isolation tank was originally called\nthe 'sensory deprivation tank'. Other names for the isolation tank include\n'flotation tank', 'John C. Lilly tank', 'REST tank', 'sensory attenuation tank',\nand 'think tank'.\n","linknr":236,"url":"Isolation_tank","recorded":1362584972,"links":29,"instances":["alternative_medicine","medicine"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Experimental psychology","Devices to alter consciousness"],"headings":["History","Tank design and usage","Types of sessions","Definition","Notable users","See also","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/I-sopod_Flotation_Tank.jpg/220px-I-sopod_Flotation_Tank.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Samadhi_tank2.jpg/210px-Samadhi_tank2.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["wellness","alternative_medicine"],["magnes